Adopted Ancestry: Halfling: Gain access to ancestry feats from another ancestry.
Adopted Ancestry: Half-Orc: Gain access to ancestry feats from another ancestry.
Adopted Ancestry: Human: Gain access to ancestry feats from another ancestry.
Advanced Blood Potency: You gain one sorcerer feat. For the purpose of prerequisites, your sorcerer level is half your character level.
Arcane Sense: Cast detect magic at will as an arcane innate spell.
Arctic Elf: You dwell deep in the frozen north and have gained incredible resilience against cold environments, granting you cold resistance equal to half your level (minimum 1).
Armor Proficiency: Become trained in a type of armor.
Armor Proficiency: Heavy armor: Become trained in a type of armor.
Armor Proficiency: Light armor: Become trained in a type of armor.
Armor Proficiency: Medium armor: Become trained in a type of armor.
Arrow Snatching: You pluck missiles from the air and hurl them back at their source.
Assurance: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Acrobatics: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Arcana: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Athletics: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Crafting: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Deception: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Diplomacy: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Intimidation: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Lore: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Medicine: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Nature: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Occultism: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Performance: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Religion: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Society: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Stealth: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Survival: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Assurance: Thievery: Receive a fixed result on a skill check.
Automatic Knowledge: Recall Knowledge as a free action once per round.
Automatic Knowledge: Arcana: Recall Knowledge as a free action once per round.
Automatic Knowledge: Crafting: Recall Knowledge as a free action once per round.
Automatic Knowledge: Lore: Recall Knowledge as a free action once per round.
Automatic Knowledge: Medicine: Recall Knowledge as a free action once per round.
Automatic Knowledge: Nature: Recall Knowledge as a free action once per round.
Automatic Knowledge: Occultism: Recall Knowledge as a free action once per round.
Automatic Knowledge: Religion: Recall Knowledge as a free action once per round.
Backup Disguise: You have a specific disguise that you keep at the ready, worn underneath your outer garment.
Bargain Hunter: Earn Income by searching for deals.
Basic Blood Potency: You gain a 1st- or 2nd-level sorcerer feat.
Basic Sorcerer Spellcasting: You gain the basic spellcasting benefits.
Battle Cry: Demoralizes foes when you roll for initiative.
Battle Medicine: Heal yourself or an ally in battle.
Battle Prayer: Calling out to your deity, you recite scripture to harm a foe.
Battle Prayer: Chaos: Calling out to your deity, you recite scripture to harm a foe.
Battle Prayer: Evil: Calling out to your deity, you recite scripture to harm a foe.
Battle Prayer: Good: Calling out to your deity, you recite scripture to harm a foe.
Battle Prayer: Law: Calling out to your deity, you recite scripture to harm a foe.
Bizarre Magic: Your magic becomes more difficult to identify.
Bless Tonic: You channel positive energy into restoratives that ward against harm.
Bless Toxin: You pour negative energy into toxins you create to further debilitate your targets.
Bloodhound Shoony: Your ancestors were famous trackers, and you carry in your blood that same gift of the hunt.
Blunt Snout: Your small, blunt snout and labyrinthine sinus system make you resistant to phenomena that assail the nose.
Bonded Animal: An animal becomes permanently helpful to you.
Brawling Focus: You know how to make the most of your attacks when fighting hand-to-hand.
Breath Control: Hold your breath longer and gain benefits against inhaled threats.
Canny Acumen: Become an expert in a saving throw or Perception.
Canny Acumen: Fortitude: Become an expert in a saving throw or Perception.
Canny Acumen: Perception: Become an expert in a saving throw or Perception.
Canny Acumen: Reflex: Become an expert in a saving throw or Perception.
Canny Acumen: Will: Become an expert in a saving throw or Perception.
Cat Fall: Treat falls as shorter than they are.
Charhide Goblin: Your ancestors have always had a connection to fire and a thicker skin, which allows you to resist burning.
Charlatan: You've learned to mimic the abilities of spellcasters by studying their flourishes and words.
Charming Liar: Improve a target's attitude with your lies.
Cliffscale Lizardfolk: Your toes are adapted for gripping and climbing.
Combat Climber: Fight more effectively as you Climb.
Confabulator: Reduce the bonuses against your repeated lies.
Connections: Leverage your connections for favors and meetings.
Continual Recovery: Treat Wounds on a patient more often.
Courtly Graces: Use Society to get along in noble Society.
Craft Anything: Ignore most requirements for Crafting items.
Crane Flutter: You interpose your arm between yourself and your opponent.
Crane Stance: You enter the stance of a crane, holding your arms in an imitation of a crane's wings.
Crushing Grab: Like a powerful constrictor, you crush targets in your unyielding grasp.
Dancing Leaf: You are as light as a leaf whirling in the breeze.
Death Warden Dwarf: Your ancestors have been tomb guardians for generations, and the power they cultivated to ward off necromancy has passed on to you.
Deflect Arrows: Your reflexes allow you to deflect ranged attacks.
Desert Elf: You live under the desert's blazing heat, gaining incredible resilience to warm environments.
Diamond Fists: Your body hardens as you combine your attacks, making your finishing blows more damaging.
Diamond Soul: You have fortified your body and mind against eldritch effects.
Diehard: Die at dying 5, rather than dying 4.
Different Worlds: Create a second identity for yourself with a different name, history, and background.
Disrupt Ki: Your strike can block a creature's inner life force.
Divine Guidance: Find guidance in the writings of your faith.
Dragon Roar: You bellow, instilling fear in your enemies.
Dragon Stance: You enter the stance of a dragon and make powerful leg strikes like a lashing dragon's tail.
Dubious Knowledge: Learn true and erroneous knowledge on failed check.
Elemental Fist: You call upon the power of the elements, infusing your ki with elemental energy and allowing your attacks to deal energy damage.
Empty Body: You transmute your body into an ethereal form.
Enduring Quickness: You move as fast and as high as the wind itself.
Enlightened Presence: You exude an aura of resolve.
Entourage: You have a small group of admirers who tend to follow you around while you're in civilized settlements.
Environmental Grace: You rapidly adapt to environments through a combination of skill, meditation, and divine grace.
Evangelize: You point out a detail that incontrovertibly supports your faith, causing a listener's mind to whirl.
Expeditious Search: Search areas in half the time.
Experienced Professional: Prevent critical failures when Earning Income.
Experienced Smuggler: Conceal items from observers more effectively.
Experienced Tracker: Track at your full Speed at a -5 penalty.
Eye of the Arclords: The Arclords of Nex have achieved a unique mastery of magic.
Fast Recovery: Regain more HP from rest, recover faster from disease and poisons.
First World Magic: Your connection to the First World grants you a primal innate spell, much like those of the fey.
Fishseeker Shoony: You come from a long line of fisherfolk and have inherited the quick reflexes necessary to nab and reel in big game.
Flurry: You have trained to unleash a devastating flurry of attacks upon your prey.
Flurry of Maneuvers: Your flurry is a combination of maneuvers.
Flying Kick: You launch yourself at a foe.
Forager: Forage for supplies to provide for multiple creatures.
Forge Dwarf: You have a remarkable adaptation to hot environments from ancestors who inhabited blazing deserts or volcanic chambers beneath the earth.
Frilled Lizardfolk: You can flare your neck frill and flex your dorsal spines, Demoralizing your foes.
Fuse Stance: You have combined two stances into a single stance all your own.
Glad-Hand: Make an Impression on a target you've just met.
Godless Healing: With limited access to divine healing magic, Rahadoumi often become adept at using ordinary medicine for when dangerous situations arise.
Golden Body: Strike harder and heal more rapidly.
Gourd Leshy: You have a large gourd for a skull.
Group Impression: Make an Impression on multiple targets at once.
Guarded Movement: Your guard is up, even while moving.
Gutsy Halfling: Your family line is known for keeping a level head and staving off fear when the chips were down, making them wise leaders and sometimes even heroes.
Hillock Halfling: Accustomed to a calm life in the hills, your people find rest and relaxation especially replenishing, particularly when indulging in creature comforts.
Impossible Technique: You execute a maneuver that defies possibility.
Improved Knockback: Your shoves cause the target to go farther.
Intimidating Prowess: Gain a bonus to physically Demoralize a target.
Inventor: Use Crafting to create item formulas.
Ironblood Stance: You enter the stance of impenetrable iron, refusing to yield to any blow.
Ironblood Surge: You steel yourself, preparing to resist oncoming attacks and using your muscles to absorb the impact.
Irongut Goblin: You can subsist on food that most folks would consider spoiled.
Irongut Goblin Fortitude: You can subsist on food that most folks would consider spoiled.
Juggle: You can Juggle items and still use your hands between tosses.
Keen Eyes: Your eyes are sharp, allowing you to make out small details about concealed or even invisible creatures that others might miss.
Ki Blast: You can unleash an impactful cone of force by channeling your ki.
Ki Rush: You can use ki to move with extraordinary speed and make yourself harder to hit.
Ki Strike: Your study of the flow of mystical energy allows you to harness it into your physical strikes.
Kip Up: Stand up for free without triggering reactions.
Knockback Strike: You focus your strength into a blow powerful enough to push an enemy away from you.
Lasting Coercion: Coerce a target into helping you longer.
Leaf Leshy: Your body is made mostly from natural foliage, and like a leaf tumbling from a tree, you land from falls with particular grace.
Legendary Linguist: Create pidgin languages to communicate with anyone.
Legendary Medic: Remove disease or the blinded, deafened, doomed, or drained condition.
Legendary Sneak: Hide and Sneak without cover or being concealed.
Legendary Thief: Steal what would normally be impossible to steal.
Lengthy Diversion: Remain hidden after you Create a Diversion.
Magical Shorthand: Learn spells quickly and at a reduced cost.
Master of Many Styles: You move between stances in an unceasing dance.
Meditative Focus: Your meditation is so effective that you can achieve a deep focus.
Meditative Wellspring: When you clear your mind, your focus comes flowing back in a powerful rush.
Mixed Maneuver: You combine two different maneuvers together into a single flowing whole.
Monastic Weaponry: You have trained with the traditional weaponry of your monastery or school.
Mortal Healing: You grant greater healing when the gods don't interfere

Impossible Flurry: You forgo precision to attack at an impossible speed.
Impossible Volley: You fire a volley at all foes in an area.
Manifold Edge: You've learned every possible edge to use against your foes.
Masterful Companion: Your animal companion shares your incredible hunting skills, allowing it to take down your shared prey with ease.
Perfect Shot: After watching the motions of combat with incredible intensity and precision, you fire at your prey at the perfect moment to deliver maximum pain.
Shadow Hunter: You blend in to your surroundings so well that others have trouble telling you apart from the terrain.
Legendary Shot: You focus on your hunted prey, perceiving angles, air resistance, and every variable that would af ect your ranged attack.
To the Ends of the Earth: Your ability to track your prey has surpassed explanation, allowing you to trace your prey's movements and predict its location with ease.
Triple Threat: You can divide your attention three ways when hunting.
Ultimate Skirmisher: You are so skilled at navigating the wild, your movement is completely unaffected by terrain.
Ranger Dedication: You have studied hunting, tracking, and wilderness survival, adding a ranger's tools to your skill set.
Basic Hunter's Trick: You gain a 1st- or 2nd-level ranger feat.
Ranger Resiliency: You gain 3 additional Hit Points for each ranger archetype class feat you have.
Master Spotter: Your proficiency rank in Perception increases to master.
Abjuration School: As an abjurer, you master the art of protection, strengthening defenses, preventing attacks, and even turning magic against itself.
Conjuration School: As a conjurer, you summon creatures and objects from places beyond, and use magic to transport to distant locales.
Divination School: As a diviner, you master remote viewing and prescience, learning information that can transform investigations, research, and battle strategies.
Enchantment School: As an enchanter, you use magic to manipulate others' minds.
Evocation School: As an evoker, you revel in the raw power of magic, using it to create and destroy with ease.
Illusion School: As an illusionist, you use magic to create images, figments, and phantasms to baffle your enemies.
Necromancy School: As a necromancer, you call upon the powers of life and death.
Transmutation School: As a transmuter, you alter the physical properties of things, transforming creatures, objects, the natural world, and even yourself at your whim.
Universalist Wizard: Instead of specializing narrowly in an arcane school, you can become a universalist wizard-by studying all the schools equally, you devote yourself to understanding the full breadth of the arcane arts.
Improved Familiar Attunement: You've long held that fine-tuning the magic that bonds wizard and familiar can improve the mystic connection, compared to the safe yet generic bond most wizards currently use.
Metamagical Experimentation: You've realized that the practice known as metamagic is a holdover from a time long ago, when wizards had to work out their own spells and variations rather than rely on spells recorded by others and passed down over the years.
Spell Blending: You theorize that spell slots are a shorthand for an underlying energy that powers all spellcasting, and you've found a way to tinker with the hierarchy of spell slots, combining them to fuel more powerful spells.
Spell Substitution: You don't accept the fact that once spells are prepared, they can't be changed until your next daily preparation, and you have uncovered a shortcut allowing you to substitute new spells for those you originally prepared.
Counterspell (Prepared): When a foe Casts a Spell and you can see its manifestations, you can use your own magic to disrupt it.
Eschew Materials: You can use clever workarounds to replicate the arcane essence of certain materials.
Familiar: An animal serves you and assists your spellcasting.
Hand of the Apprentice: You can magically hurl your weapon at your foe.
Reach Spell: You can extend the range of your spells.
Widen Spell: You manipulate the energy of your spell, causing it to spread out and affect a wider area.
Cantrip Expansion (Prepared): Study broadens your range of simple spells.
Conceal Spell: Hiding your gestures and incantations within other speech and movement, you attempt to conceal the fact that you are casting a spell.
Enhanced Familiar: You infuse your familiar with additional primal energy, increasing its abilities.
Bespell Weapon: You siphon the residual energy from the last spell you cast into one weapon you're wielding.
Linked Focus: You have linked your bonded item to the well of energy that powers your school spells.
Silent Spell: You've learned how to cast many of your spells without speaking the words of power you would normally need to provide.
Spell Penetration: You've studied ways of overcoming the innate magical resistance that certain powerful creatures have.
Advanced School Spell: You gain access to a powerful new school spell depending on your arcane school.
Advanced School Spell: Abjuration: You gain access to a powerful new school spell depending on your arcane school.
Advanced School Spell: Conjuration: You gain access to a powerful new school spell depending on your arcane school.
Advanced School Spell: Divination: You gain access to a powerful new school spell depending on your arcane school.
Advanced School Spell: Enchantment: You gain access to a powerful new school spell depending on your arcane school.
Advanced School Spell: Evocation: You gain access to a powerful new school spell depending on your arcane school.
Advanced School Spell: Illusion: You gain access to a powerful new school spell depending on your arcane school.
Advanced School Spell: Necromancy: You gain access to a powerful new school spell depending on your arcane school.
Advanced School Spell: Transmutation: You gain access to a powerful new school spell depending on your arcane school.
Bond Conservation: By carefully manipulating the arcane energies stored in your bonded item as you drain it, you can conserve just enough power to cast another, slightly weaker spell.
Universal Versatility: You can access the fundamental abilities of any school of magic.
Overwhelming Energy: You alter your spells to overcome resistances.
Quickened Casting: You are able to quickly cast a spell.
Scroll Savant: During your daily preparations, you can create two temporary scrolls containing arcane spells from your spellbook.
Clever Counterspell: You creatively apply your prepared spells to counterspell a much wider variety of your opponents' magic.
Magic Sense (Wizard): You have a literal sixth sense for magic.
Magic Sense (Sorcerer): You have a literal sixth sense for magic.
Bonded Focus: Your connection to your bonded item increases your focus pool.
Reflect Spell: You cause a spell to fire back at its caster.
Superior Bond: When you draw upon your bonded item, you can leave a bit of energy within it for later use.
Effortless Concentration: You can maintain a spell with hardly a thought.
Spell Tinker: You've learned to alter choices you make when casting spells on yourself.
Infinite Possibilities: You've found a way to prepare a spell slot that exists in your mind as many different possibilities at once.
Reprepare Spell: You've discovered how to reuse some of your spell slots over and over.
Archwizard's Might: You have mastered the greatest secrets of arcane magic.
Metamagic Mastery: Altering your spells doesn't take any longer than casting them normally.
Spell Combination: You can merge spells, producing multiple effects with a single casting.
Wizard Dedication: You have dabbled in the arcane arts and, through discipline and academic study, learned how to cast a few spells.
Arcane School Spell: Select one arcane school of magic. You gain the school's initial school spell.
Arcane School Spell: Abjuration: You gain the abjurations school's protective ward spell.
Arcane School Spell: Conjuration: You gain the conjurations school's augment summoning spell.
Arcane School Spell: Divination: You gain the divinations school's diviner's sight spell.
Arcane School Spell: Enchantment: You gain the enchantment school's charming words spell.
Arcane School Spell: Evocation: You gain the evocations school's force bolt spell.
Arcane School Spell: Illusion: You gain the illusion school's protective warped terrain.
Arcane School Spell: Necromancy: You gain the necromancy school's call of the grave spell.
Arcane School Spell: Transmutation: You gain the transmutations school's physical boost spell.
Basic Arcana: You gain a 1st- or 2nd-level wizard feat of your choice.
Basic Wizard Spellcasting: You gain the basic spellcasting benefits.
Arcane Breadth: You can cast more arcane spells each day.
Expert Wizard Spellcasting: You gain the expert spellcasting benefits.
Master Wizard Spellcasting: You gain the master spellcasting benefits.
Ruffian Racket: You prefer to strong-arm or intimidate others rather than rely on finesse or fancy tricks.
Scoundrel Racket: You use fast-talking, flattery, and a silver tongue to avoid danger and escape tricky situations.
Thief Racket: Nothing beats the thrill of taking something that belongs to someone else, especially if you can do so completely unnoticed.
Nimble Dodge: You deftly dodge out of the way.
Trap Finder: You have an intuitive sense that alerts you to the dangers and presence of traps.
Twin Feint: You make a dazzling series of attacks with both weapons, using the first attack to throw your foe of guard against a second attack at a different angle.
You're Next: After downing a foe, you menacingly remind another foe that you're coming after them next.
Brutal Beating: The brutality of your critical hits shakes your foes' confidence.
Distracting Feint: Your Feints are far more distracting than normal, drawing your foes' attention and allowing you and your allies to take greater advantage.
Minor Magic: You've dabbled in a variety of tricks, gaining minor magical abilities from a particular tradition.
Minor Magic: Arcane: You've dabbled in a variety of tricks, gaining two common arcane cantrips.
Minor Magic: Divine: You've dabbled in a variety of tricks, gaining two common divine cantrips.
Minor Magic: Occult: You've dabbled in a variety of tricks, gaining two common occult cantrips.
Minor Magic: Primal: You've dabbled in a variety of tricks, gaining two common primal cantrips.
Mobility: You move in a way that denies your enemies the opportunity to retaliate.
Quick Draw: You draw your weapon and attack with the same motion.
Unbalancing Blow: Interweaving your most powerful attacks in a graceful flow, you temporarily unbalance your foes. Whenever your Strike is a critical hit and deals damage, the target is flat-footed against your attacks until the end of your next turn.
Battle Assessment: With careful observation during battle, you identify an enemy's strengths and weaknesses.
Dread Striker: You capitalize on your enemies' fear to slip past their defenses.
Magical Trickster: You can sneak spells past your foes' defenses as easily as any blade.
Poison Weapon: You apply poison to a weapon.
Reactive Pursuit: You keep pace with a retreating foe.
Scout's Warning: You visually or audibly warn your allies of danger.
Gang Up: You and your allies harry an opponent in concert.
Light Step: You aren't bothered by tricky footing.
Skirmish Strike: Your feet and weapon move in tandem.
Twist the Knife: After stabbing your opponent in a weak spot, you tear the wound open.
Blind-Fight: Your battle instincts make you more aware of concealed and invisible opponents.
Delay Trap: You can jam the workings of a trap to delay its effects.
Improved Poison Weapon: You deliver poisons in ways that maximize their harmful effects.
Nimble Roll: You throw yourself into a roll to escape imminent danger.
Opportune Backstab: When your enemy is hit by your ally, you capitalize upon the distraction.
Sidestep: You deftly step out of the way of an attack, letting the blow continue to the creature next to you.
Sly Striker: Your attacks deal more damage, even against creatures that aren't flat-footed.
Precise Debilitation: You carefully aim and gracefully deliver your debilitations.
Sneak Savant: It is almost impossible to spot you without taking effort to look.
Tactical Debilitations: You learn new debilitations that grant you tactical advantages against your foes.
Vicious Debilitations: The debilitations you dish out seriously impair your foes.
Critical Debilitations: Your debilitations are especially effective on your most powerful attacks.
Fantastic Leap: You launch yourself through the air at a foe.
Felling Shot: Your ranged attacks can shoot an unprepared foe right out of the air.
Reactive Interference: You reflexively foil an enemy's response.
Spring from the Shadows: Leaping out from hiding, you assail your target when they least expect it.
Defensive Roll: Dropping into a roll to disperse the force of the blow, you can partially evade a lethal attack and stay conscious.
Instant Opening: You distract your opponent with a few choice words or a rude gesture.
Leave an Opening: When you hit hard enough, you leave an opening so your ally can jump in on the action.
Sense the Unseen: When you look for foes, you can catch even the slightest cues.
Blank Slate: Your deceptions confound even the most powerful mortal divinations.
Cloud Step: Using fantastic acrobatic skill, you can walk for brief stretches across insubstantial surfaces.
Cognitive Loophole: You can find a loophole in a mental effect to temporarily overcome it.
Dispelling Slice: Your sneak attack slices through the threads binding magic to a target.
Perfect Distraction: You use clever tactics to mislead your foes as you sneak away. You Sneak while leaving a decoy behind.
Implausible Infiltration: You find tiny holes or imperfections that no one else could see and try to somehow fit yourself through them.
Powerful Sneak: You have learned to exploit your enemies' lowered defenses.
Trickster's Ace: You have a contingency in your back pocket for desperate situations.
Hidden Paragon: When you put your mind to slipping out of sight, you disappear completely.
Impossible Striker: Your attacks are swift and deadly beyond explanation.
Reactive Distraction: You reactively switch with your decoy to foil your foe.
Rogue Dedication: You've learned to sneak, steal, and disable traps. With time and luck, you'll become capable of moving through the shadows, striking unseen, and escaping without notice.
Basic Trickery: You gain a 1st- or 2nd-level rogue feat.
Sneak Attacker: You gain the sneak attack class feature, except it deals 1d4 damage.
Skill Mastery: You gain 3 additional Hit Points for each ranger archetype class feat you have.
Uncanny Dodge: You gain the deny advantage class feature.
Evasiveness: Your proficiency rank for Reflex saves increases to master.
Enigma Muse: Your muse is a mystery, driving you to uncover the hidden secrets of the multiverse.
Maestro Muse: Your muse is a virtuoso, inspiring you to greater heights.
Polymath Muse: Your muse is a jack of all trades, flitting between skills and pursuits.
Bardic Lore: Your studies make you informed on every subject.
Lingering Composition: By adding a flourish, you make your compositions last longer.
Versatile Performance: You can rely on the grandeur of your performances rather than ordinary social skills.
Cantrip Expansion (Spontaneous): Study broadens your range of simple spells.
Esoteric Polymath: You keep a book of occult spells, similar to a wizard's spellbook.
Inspire Competence: You learn the inspire competence composition cantrip, which aids your allies' skills.
Loremaster's Etude: You magically unlock memories, making them easier to recall.
Multifarious Muse: Your muse doesn't fall into a single label.
Multifarious Muse: Enigma Muse: Your muse doesn't fall into a single label.
Multifarious Muse: Maestro Muse: Your muse doesn't fall into a single label.
Multifarious Muse: Polymath Muse: Your muse doesn't fall into a single label.
Inspire Defense: You learn the inspire defense composition cantrip, which protects you and allies.
Melodious Spell: You subtly weave your spellcasting into your performance.
Triple Time: You learn to speed up yourself and your allies with your performance.
Versatile Signature: You're always tweaking your available repertoire.
Dirge of Doom: You learn to frighten your enemies with your performance.
Harmonize: You can perform multiple compositions simultaneously.
Eclectic Skill: Your broad experiences translate to a range of skills.
Inspire Heroics: Your performances inspire even greater deeds in your allies.
Know-It-All: Your knowledge of the world expands beyond what you have read.
House of Imaginary Walls: You erect an imaginary barrier others believe to be real.
Unusual Composition: You can translate the emotion and power of a composition to other mediums.
Eclectic Polymath: Your flexible mind can quickly shift spells.
Inspirational Focus: Your connection to your muse has granted you unusual focus.
Silver's Refrain: Learn the silver's refrain composition cantrip.
Allegro: You can quicken your allies with a fast-paced performance.
Soothing Ballad: You soothe your allies' wounds with the power of your performance.
True Hypercognition: Your mind works at an incredible pace.
Studious Capacity: Your continued study of occult magic has increased your magical capacity.
Deep Lore: Your repertoire is vast, containing far more spells than usual.
Eternal Composition: The world is a stage upon which you are always playing.
Impossible Polymath: Your esoteric formulas are so unusual that they allow you to dabble in magic from diverse traditions.
Fatal Aria: Your songs overwhelm the target with unbearable emotion.
Ringmaster's Introduction: You announce the triggering ally with a litany of their legendary achievements, spurring them to action.
Song of the Fallen: Gain the song of the fallen focus spell.
Symphony of the Muses: You are able to weave countless performances together into a solo symphony.
Bard Dedication: A muse has called you to dabble in occult lore, allowing you to cast a few spells. The deeper you delve, the more powerful your performances become.
Basic Bard Spellcasting: You gain the basic spellcasting benefits.
Basic Muse's Whispers: You gain a 1st- or 2nd-level bard feat.
Counter Perform: You gain the counter performance composition spell.
Inspirational Performance: You gain the inspire courage composition cantrip.
Occult Breadth: Your repertoire expands, and you can cast more occult spells each day.
Expert Bard Spellcasting: You gain the expert spellcasting benefits.
Master Bard Spellcasting: You gain the master spellcasting benefits.
Bouncy Goblin: You have a particular elasticity that makes it easy for you to bounce and squish.
City Scavenger: You know that the greatest treasures often look like refuse, and you scoff at those who throw away perfectly good scraps.
Fang Sharpener: You have filed your teeth into jagged points and have an unusually powerful jaw, making your mouth a dangerous weapon.
Goblin Lore: You've picked up skills and tales from your goblin community.
Goblin Scuttle: You take advantage of your ally's movement to adjust your position.
Goblin Song: You sing annoying goblin songs, distracting your foes with silly and repetitive lyrics.
Goblin Weapon Familiarity: Others might look upon them with disdain, but you know that the weapons of your people are as effective as they are sharp.
Hard Tail: Your tail is much stronger than most, and you can lash out with it with the strength of a whip.
Junk Tinker: You can make useful tools out of even twisted or rusted scraps.
Rough Rider: You are especially good at riding traditional goblin mounts.
Very Sneaky: Taller folk rarely pay attention to the shadows at their feet, and you take full advantage of this.
Ankle Bite: Whenever someone grabs onto you, you instinctively bite down hard.
Chosen of Lamashtu: You bear the favor and blessings of Lamashtu, the Mother of Monsters.
Fey Influence: Your exposure to fey influence has given you some primal magic
Goblin Weapon Frenzy: You know how to wield your people's vicious weapons.
Tail Spin: You excel at using your tail as a weapon to upend your foes.
Torch Goblin: You've spent enough time on fire that you know how to use it to your advantage.
Tree Climber (Goblin): Your time in forest or jungle canopies has taught you how to scramble across branches with sure feet.
Cave Climber: After years of crawling and climbing through caverns, you can climb easily anywhere you go.
Freeze It!: You are no rime hag or Jadwiga, but the magic of the north has still left a mark on you.
Roll with It: When you take a big hit, your foe bounces you around like a rubber ball, but you escape the worst of the blow.
Scalding Spit: Your bodily fluids burn with surprising volatility, as if you ran on oil instead of blood.
Skittering Scuttle: You can scuttle farther and faster when maneuvering alongside allies.
Goblin Weapon Expertise: Your goblin affinity blends with your class training, granting you great skill with goblin weapons.
Unbreakable-er Goblin: As hard as most unbreakable goblins are to break, you are that much harder to break.
Very, Very Sneaky: Your ability to hide is so great, you can disappear straight from vision.
Adroit Manipulation: You've fiddled with knots, locks, and blacksmith's puzzles since you were a child to give your hands something to do.
Distracting Shadows: You have learned to remain hidden by using larger folk as a distraction to avoid drawing attention to yourself.
Halfling Lore: You've dutifully learned important skills passed down through generations of halfling tradition.
Halfling Luck: Your happy-go-lucky nature makes it seem like misfortune avoids you, and to an extent, that might even be true.
Halfling Weapon Familiarity: You favor traditional halfling weapons, so you've learned how to use them more effectively.
Innocuous: Halflings have been unobtrusive assistants of larger folk for untold ages, and your people count on this assumption of innocence.
Intuitive Cooperation: You are accustomed to working alongside others, relying on each other to get by.
Sure Feet: Whether keeping your balance or scrambling up a tricky climb, your hairy, calloused feet easily find purchase.
Titan Slinger: You have learned how to use your sling to fell enormous creatures.
Unassuming Dedication: Your family instilled the values of care and patience into you from a young age.
Unfettered Halfling: You were forced into service as a laborer, but you've since escaped and have trained to ensure you'll never be caught again.
Watchful Halfling: Your communal lifestyle causes you to pay close attention to the people around you.
Cultural Adaptability: During your adventures, you've honed your ability to adapt to the culture of the predominant ancestry around you.
Easily Dismissed: You are practiced at blending into the background of the streets and halls of larger folk to ensure that you are overlooked.
Halfling Ingenuity: While your willingness to dig into a task you know little about might get you into trouble, your incredible luck often saves you from danger.
Halfling Weapon Trickster: You are particularly adept at fighting with your people's favored weapons.
Shared Luck (Halfling): You are evidence that it's lucky to travel with a halfling.
Cunning Climber: Whether you are climbing a ship's rigging, a jungle tree, or a clock tower, you have an uncanny knack for finding footholds and handholds where larger creatures can't.
Fade Away: Your ability to blend into the background allows you to fade away entirely or appear innocuous even to magical effects.
Guiding Luck: Your luck guides you to look the right way and aim your blows unerringly.
Helpful Halfling: When you aid a friend with a task, you find many ways to help and avoid interfering.
Irrepressible: You are easily able to ward off attempts to play on your fears and emotions.
Ceaseless Shadows: You excel at going unnoticed, especially among a crowd.
Cobble Dancer: You know how to take advantage of foes thrown off-balance by unstable flooring, loose cobblestones, or similar impediments.
Halfling Weapon Expertise: Your halfling affinity blends with your class training, granting you great skill with halfling weapons.
Incredible Luck (Halfling): Even other halflings consider you to be particularly lucky.
Adapted Cantrip: Through study of multiple magical traditions, you've altered a spell to suit your spellcasting style.
Arcane Tattoos: You have tattoos on your body corresponding to one of the ancient Thassilonian schools of magic.
Arcane Tattoos: Abjuration: You have tattoos on your body corresponding to one of the ancient Thassilonian schools of magic.
Arcane Tattoos: Conjuration: You have tattoos on your body corresponding to one of the ancient Thassilonian schools of magic.
Arcane Tattoos: Enchantment: You have tattoos on your body corresponding to one of the ancient Thassilonian schools of magic.
Arcane Tattoos: Evocation: You have tattoos on your body corresponding to one of the ancient Thassilonian schools of magic.
Arcane Tattoos: Illusion: You have tattoos on your body corresponding to one of the ancient Thassilonian schools of magic.
Arcane Tattoos: Necromancy: You have tattoos on your body corresponding to one of the ancient Thassilonian schools of magic.
Arcane Tattoos: Transmutation: You have tattoos on your body corresponding to one of the ancient Thassilonian schools of magic.
Cooperative Nature: The short human life span lends perspective and has taught you from a young age to set aside differences and work with others to achieve greatness.
Courteous Comeback: You grew up in the proud Padishah Empire, where even insults have a certain poetic wit.
Devil's Advocate: You know more about the habits of devils than is entirely safe.
Dragon Spit: Many Tian-Dan claim to have dragon blood in their veins, and in your case, this is true—you can spit energy, and you might have an especially visible sign of your draconic heritage.
General Training: Your adaptability manifests in your mastery of a range of useful abilities.
Gloomseer: Gloom holds few terrors for you, and the pall of darkness over Nidal has made you comfortable in dim light.
Haughty Obstinacy: Your powerful ego makes it harder for others to order you around.
Keep Up Appearances: Taldan pride means you never show weakness.
Know Oneself: You center yourself and call to mind the Vudrani monastic ideals of mindfulness and self-knowledge.
Natural Ambition: You were raised to be ambitious and always reach for the stars, leading you to progress quickly in your chosen field.
Natural Skill: Your ingenuity allows you to learn a wide variety of skills.
Quah Bond: You grew up among the Shoanti tribes, with the spirits watching over you, and they offer you guidance.
Saoc Astrology: The ancient Saoc Brethren were the masters of astrology, and while your knowledge may be but a pale shadow of their wisdom, it still comes in handy.
Tupilaq Carver: You know the truth behind old stories that tell of sending a fetish of bone and sinew to seek vengeance.
Unconventional Weaponry: You've familiarized yourself with a particular weapon, potentially from another ancestry or culture.
Viking Shieldbearer: You trained with shields and weapons as soon as you were old enough to hold them, eager to win honor and glory for yourself.
Witch Warden: You and your family have fought long and hard against witches, particularly the winter witches of Irrisen, and you've learned to be wary of their curses and the otherworldly powers their patrons grant.
Adaptive Adept: You've continued adapting your magic to blend your class's tradition with your adapted tradition.
Clever Improviser: You've learned how to handle situations when you're out of your depth.
Darkseer: Zon-Kuthon smiles upon you—even if you curse his name—granting you pitch-black eyes that allow you to see in shadows and darkness.
Ornate Tattoo: You expand your tattoos to encompass greater magic.
Wavetouched Paragon: You have been blessed by the sea, granting you the ability to swim like a fish.
Cooperative Soul: You have developed a soul-deep bond with your comrades and maintain an even greater degree of cooperation with them.
Dragon Prince: The blood of the Dragon Kings runs strong in your veins.
Heir of the Saoc: In the past, you would have been a proud initiate of the Saoc Brethren.
Incredible Improvisation: A stroke of brilliance gives you a major advantage with a skill despite your inexperience.
Multitalented: You've learned to split your focus between multiple classes with ease.
Shory Aeromancer: Your ancestors hailed from the flying cities of the Shory, and a few simple tricks have come down through the ages to you.
Virtue-Forged Tattoos: Your tattoos are a work of eldritch genius, a masterpiece of art, magic, and skin.
Irriseni Ice-Witch: You can trace your direct descent from one of the Queens of Irrisen and thus from Baba Yaga herself.
Shadow Pact: Thousands of years ago, your ancestors made a pact with Zon-Kuthon.
Shory Aerialist: Unique in Golarion's history, the Shory people developed fighting styles dedicated to combat in the air.
Unconventional Expertise: You've continued to advance your powers using your unconventional weapon.
Ancestral Longevity: You have accumulated a vast array of lived knowledge over the years.
Elemental Wrath: You are so attuned to the land that you can call forth a bolt of energy from your surroundings.
Elven Lore: You've studied in traditional elven arts, learning about arcane magic and the world around you.
Elven Verve: While all elves are immune to the paralyzing touch of ghouls, you can shake off flesh-numbing magic of all kinds.
Elven Weapon Familiarity: You favor bows and other elegant weapons.
Forlorn: Watching your friends age and die fills you with moroseness that protects you against harmful emotions.
Otherworldly Magic: Your elven magic manifests as a simple arcane spell, even if you aren't formally trained in magic.
Share Thoughts: You have an uncanny knack of communicating with other elves without speaking, though this habit that is often uncomfortable to observers.
Unwavering Mien: Your mystic control and meditations allow you to resist external influences upon your consciousness.
Wildborn Magic: You have learned to access the old magic of wild places.
Woodcraft: You have a innate familiarity with forested areas.
Ageless Patience: You work at a pace born from longevity that enhances your thoroughness.
Defiance Unto Death: You loathe the alghollthus and their mind magic, and you've been trained to be willing to die rather than give into mental manipulation.
Elven Instincts: Your senses let you react rapidly.
Elven Weapon Elegance: You are attuned to the weapons of your elven ancestors and are particularly deadly when using them.
Forest Stealth: You are skilled at quickly hiding behind bits of underbrush or foliage.
Wildborn Adept: The whispers of the jungle grant you more diverse access to simple primal magic.
Brightness Seeker: Once per day, you can spend 10 minutes studying your surroundings in search of omens related to a particular course of action to cast augury as an innate divine spell.
Elf Step: You move in a graceful dance, and even your steps are broad.
Expert Longevity: You've continued to refine the knowledge and skills you've gained through your life.
Sense Thoughts: You have an even stranger knack for knowing what other people are thinking.
Elven Weapon Expertise: Your elven affinity blends with your class training, granting you great skill with elven weapons.
Universal Longevity: You've perfected your ability to keep up with all the skills you've learned over your long life.
Wandering Heart: While all elves adapt to their environments over time, you have traveled so widely and become attuned to so many environs that your body now changes more rapidly than other elves.
Lizardfolk Lore: You listened carefully to the tales passed down among your community.
Marsh Runner: You are adept at moving through marshy terrain.
Parthenogenic Hatchling: You were hatched from an unfertilized egg during hard times for your people, and you are a biological copy of your mother.
Razor Claws: Your have honed your claws to be deadly.
Reptile Speaker: You hear the sounds of reptiles as language.
Tail Whip: By birth or through training, your tail is strong enough to make for a powerful melee weapon.
Gecko's Grip: You stick to walls with a preternatural grip.
Iruxi Unarmed Cunning: You make the most of your iruxi unarmed attacks.
Shed Tail: You can shed your tail to escape.
Swift Swimmer: You swim faster than most iruxi.
Terrain Advantage: You can take advantage of the terrain to bypass foes' defenses.
Iruxi Unarmed Expertise: Your unarmed attacks blend tradition and training.
Elf Atavism: Your elven blood runs particularly strong, granting you features far more elven than those of a typical half-elf.
Round Ears: Your elven lineage is subtle enough that you look barely different from other humans, and you've learned to use that to your advantage.
Sociable: You're extremely extroverted, and you often spend your time carousing or otherwise socializing.
Inspire Imitation: Your own actions inspire your allies to great achievements.
Supernatural Charm: The elven magic in your blood manifests as a force you can use to become more appealing or alluring.
Monstrous Peacemaker: Your dual human and orc nature has given you a unique perspective.
Orc Ferocity: Fierceness in battle runs through your blood, and you refuse to fall from your injuries.
Orc Sight: Your orc blood is strong enough to grant you the keen vision of your orc forebears.
Orc Superstition: You defend yourself against magic by relying on techniques derived from orc cultural superstitions.
Orc Weapon Familiarity: In combat, you favor the brutal weapons that are traditional for your orc ancestors.
Overlooked Mastermind: Many consider half-orcs little more than dumb brutes.
Orc Weapon Carnage: You are brutally efficient with the weapons of your orc ancestors.
Victorious Vigor: Your victories in battle fill you with pride and imbue you with the energy to fight a bit longer despite your wounds.
Pervasive Superstition: You steep yourself in superstition and practice ancient orc mental exercises for shrugging off the effects of magic.
Incredible Ferocity: Given time to collect yourself after a near-death scrape, you can rebuild your ferocity and withstand additional finishing blows.
Orc Weapon Expertise: Your orc affinity blends with your class training, granting you great skill with orc weapons.
Mountain's Stoutness: Your hardiness lets you withstand more punishment than most before going down.
